Nov 4 2009 	love this hotel	I've stayed at this hotel twice and I loved it each time. The staff is very friendly and helpful. The breakfast buffet has so much variety and the chinese restaurant was great! Its very close to the silk alley market which was nice so we didnt have to get a cab. The gardens outside were great with real ducks! I would stay at this hotel again and again!	
Oct 11 2009 	Nicely situated hotel	The hotel is clean and well appointed. Bedrooms are fairly basic and a bit tired in need of some decoration. Check in staff were quite rude and not very helpfull. The lack of English can make communicating very difficult. The hotel has a lot of trainee staff who we found were excellent. They made the effort to use what little English they had to converse with us. Something that the other hotel staff did not even attempt. The opera is an absolute must, an excellent evening entertainment. The restaraunts in the hotel were average with the best being the Apollo but be prepared to be served lukewarm meals. The location of the hotel is quite good for those who like to do a lot of walking to take in sights. Nearest metro station a good 20 min walk but access to all major attractions could be got to from here.	
Oct 5 2009	Strictly average	Our tour stayed at this hotel, it was billed at 4 star, but this is not an international 4 star rating. The rooms were clean but in need of some refurbishment, especially the hall carpets were very dirty in places. Ask for a non-smoking room if this is important to you - they probably won't guarantee it though! We had rooms that had definately been smoked in and even a room that is smoke free will open onto a corridor which at times can be hazy with smoke - it seems guests go out in the corridor to smoke. Beds were comfortable but pillows hard and weighed a ton - never come across anything like it, you can get a soft pillow if you ask enough times. There was a water dispenser in the room, both hot and cold, which was very useful till on the second day when plugged into the socket (too noisy to leave on all night) it blew up and shorted out all the lights. A replacement was brought quite swiftly but it then proceeded to leak all over the floor. The air conditioning was turned off mid stay as they decided it wasn't necessary any more. Day temperatures were mid 20s and we disagreed. One member of the party managed to get a fan delivered to the room after it was found the windows had been screwed shut and could not be opened. The breakfast is quite good - nasty 'juice' but lots of bacon, eggs etc. plus local food if you like. We did not try the restaurants. The Business Centre is quite expensive for internet connection and when they decide it is time to close they just switch your connection off without warning! They were most accommodating in organising us a packed breakfast one morning when we had a 4am start - it took the chef, banqueting manager and another manager to organise it but they did a great job of a bacon sandwiches! There is a convenient supermarket across the road for soft drinks etc and the hotel's location is quite near both the famous Qianmen Quanjude Roast Duck Restaurant in one direction and Tianmen Square in another - both about 10 minutes by taxi. Whilst English was spoken in the hotel most of the staff wore &quot;Trainee&quot; badges and they definately needed some training on customer service.	
Sep 7 2009 	Great Value for Money	At just $50 per night including breakfast, you really can't go wrong. Hotel is nicely decorated but not over the top, rooms and corridors are spotlessly clean, buffet breakfast is pretty standard fare but there is a decent choice between Western and Chinese food. Location is excellent with just a short cab ride to Tianmen square, Temple of Heaven and for those interested in shopping, the Pearl Market. There is also Beijing opera in the hotel if you like that sort of thing.Internet connection is quite expensive, but other than that I would have no hesitation in staying here again.	
