Aug 17 2008	Boring - but functional and clean	Qianmen is a tourist hotel, several streets/blocks away from the shopping area and what I believe is the best city of Beijing. You need to take a taxi. However, there is some shops, a McDonalds and a supermarket close by. The hotel overall is very boring, lobby area is without charm and I was really missing a nice bar spot to relax and join a cocktail or two with friends. The bar is there, but it is not welcoming you. Room with good standard equipment, clean and nothing to complain, more then its boring and the brown colors just feeling to much sometimes. Breakfast buffet nice and with several choices. I had problem to pay with my credit card upon check out, and they wasn't to helpful with this.We stayed here during a package trip to China and would never stay here again, just because I prefer a more hip and upper standard hotels - and there are several choices in Beijing for a not to much supplement.	
