Jul 21 2007 	Good tourists location in Beijing	Arrived off an early morning flight and were made very welcome, and room ready after breakfast. That's a good start! The room is good, if in need of a some detail cleaning ;-) Free internet is not free, but I'm learning that it's like that in China. Much advertising and/or internet offers don't actually match what is on offer when you get there. The location is good, we walked from the Forbidden City to the hotel one day in about 45 minutes; and walked to the Temple of Heaven about 30 minutes another day. The area seems pretty safe to wander (all of China does actually) and there was a couple of good restaurants nearby. The hotels own restaurants are above average too.	
Jul 2 2007 	Can recommend this hotel	Like many of the reviewers, we found this hotel lovely. There was a pleasant feel about the place, staff were friendly, fixtures &amp; fittings excellant. Good size, quality beds &amp; bathroom.The only slight downside was the Marco Polo restaurant, which served the western breakfast - we followed a large group in for an early breakfast &amp; clearly the staff had made no attempt to clear any tables. It is quite small (without any natural light) - so if you have a strict timetable to meet - be warned!We had a one meal in the Chinese restaurant in the hotel - ground floor, which was fine - but otherwise we went out. You must visit the &quot;ducK&quot; restaurant (Quanjade Roast Duck Restaurant)- its 30 mins walk - its easier &amp; certainly cooler to take a taxi for 10 Y. For a local meal, we went to one recommended by the concierge - turn right outside hotel, cross the road by pelican crossing to the other side of Yongan road (i.e. on opposite side to large supermarket) and carry on down road for about 100 m - it is the 2nd restaurant &amp; has pink tablecloths (1st restaurant does not have any tablecloths &amp; is clearly not as popular with the locals)	
Apr 11 2007 	Very pleased	Reasonably priced. Very nice hotel, beautiful lobby and corridors, comfortable room, clean with all amenities. We paid extra for internet in the room. Subway is about 1 km away, but city bus service to subway (#14 or 15) is frequent and will get you there if you choose not to walk. Some good local food nearby (a little place at 48-2 Beiwei Lu serves excellent porridge, breakfast/ lunch dishes, inexpensive and clean) and Weiduomei Bakery at corner of Hufang Lu and Beiwei Lu makes fresh, excellent pastries, and the cost is very low. Hotel food is decent and good, but not outstanding for the price.	
Feb 2 2007	Great for Group Travel	We stayed here a part of an Australian school group travelling through China and had a fantastic experience. The hotel staff were always friendly and spoke fair to good english. If they weren't sure what you were asking they always checked with someone else. The rooms were really spacious and always clean. Buffet breakfast daily was great with a wide selection available to suit everyone. Also close to restaurants which were fantastic for food and price. The supermarket across the road was good for supplies and an experience on it's own. Although not within walking distance to venues the public transport was a great experience. We always travelled in groups so weren't worried about going out to restaurants etc. at night. The staff will always write down where you want to go in chinese to give to taxis which is a big help and the hotel's card is all you have to give drivers to get home. Staff have a good idea of how much it will cost also which is good to get sorted out with the driver before you start. Taxis come to the hotel door. Hawkers in the street outside are part of the experience and will leave you alone if you say &quot;No Thank You&quot;. Local shops are fairly priced also so don't be afraid to have a look. Would definately recommend this hotel to anyone travelling to Beijing and would stay there again!	
Jul 23 2006 	Terrific hotel	My wife, 20 month old daughter and I stayed here for 3 nights on our trip to Beijing from Australia. We found the hotel rooms to be very large and extremely comfortable. When we arrived a very new looking cot had already been set up for us in the room (and was provided at no charge) which was terrific.Breakfast was buffet style and had everything you could want. There is a large, locally used, supermarket across the road where we were able to buy milk, juice, nappies etc. it was a great experience just to shop there.We were a short Taxi ride to all tourist venues. (less than 10 minutes and about 10- 12 Yuen) and could possibly have walked to most if we were without our 20 month old!! The hotel is out of the CBD in south Beijing and for us this allowed us to see more of the local Chinese then just being in a CBD area in a western hotel.All facilities were great and the staff were always very helpful.Highly recommended for tourists, and families.	
